frameDefinitions: The lexical units in this frame are descriptions of a Cognizer's Attitude about or outlook on a State_of_affairs.     ''
A Cognizer would engage in an Activity if asked or otherwise prompted to do so.
A Cognizer makes a Decision, which may be about an entity or a course of action.
An Agent schedules an Event to take place at a specified Scheduled_time and Place.
This frame is concerned with the likelihood of a Hypothetical_event occurring.
This frame has to do with the bias or lack of bias of a Judge making an assessment concerning two or more Sides.
frameExamples: Carl is becoming more <t>pessimistic</t> about the negotiations every day.
The court is <t>willing</t> to depart from the usual range of sentencing .
Gina <t>scheduled</t> a dentist appointment for Monday in Berkeley.
It is <t>likely</t> that he'll arrive late.
listRoleDefinitions: The person whose <fen>Attitude</fen> about a <fen>State_of_affairs</fen> is being expressed.
The outlook or viewpoint expressed by the <fen>Cognizer</fen>.
An event, topic, or situation about which the <fen>Cognizer</fen> has an <fen>Attitude</fen>.
The Time interval during which the <fen>Cognizer</fen> has the <fen>Attitude</fen> about the <fen>State_of_affairs</fen>.
The <fen>Cognizer</fen> is the individual that is willing to engage in the <fen>Activity</fen>.
The <fen>Activity</fen> is what the <fen>Cognizer</fen> would do under certain circumstances.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Cognizer</fen> is willing to engage in the <fen>Activity</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the <fen>Cognizer</fen> is willing to engage in the <fen>Activity</fen>.
The <fen>Cognizer</fen> decides on a course of action.
<fen>Decision</fen> identifies the entity or course of action upon which the <fen>Cognizer</fen> decides.
The time or time period over which the <fen>Cognizer</fen> makes the decision.
The place where the <fen>Cognizer</fen> makes the decision.
The sentient being who schedules an <fen>Event</fen> to take place at a <fen>Time</fen> and <fen>Place</fen>.
The incident that the <fen>Agent</fen> has scheduled to take place at a <fen>Time</fen> and <fen>Place</fen>.
The time at which the <fen>Event</fen> is scheduled to take place.
This role describes the time at which the scheduling occurs.
The location where the <fen>Agent</fen> has scheduled the <fen>Event</fen> to take place.
The state of affairs or occurrence whose likelihood is assessed.
When the event occurs.
Where the event takes place.
This Frame Element marks the person whose objectivity in making assesment is being evaluated.
This Frame Element marks one of the <fen>Sides</fen> in a dispute or one of the alternatives in a situation of choice.
This Frame Element marks phrases jointly expressing both <fen>Sides</fen> in a dispute or all of the alternatives in a situation of choice.
The second-mentioned of the <fen>Sides</fen> to a dispute or alternatives in a situation of choice.
This Frame Element marks expressions that indicate how the bias of the <fen>Judge</fen> expresses itself in their behavior or actions.
The <fen>Dispute</fen> is the situation in which there is some conflict between two sides.
The individual whose point of view is taken in assigning the judgment denoted by the target.
The <fen>Expressor</fen> is the body part or action by a body part which indicates the character of the <fen>Decision_maker</fen>.
This role denotes the time when the partiality occurs.
listRoleExamples: <fex>Americans</fex> are optimistic despite the climbing unemployment rate.
Michelle had a somewhat negative <fex>outlook</fex> on the direction her life was heading.
<fex>The economy</fex> looks quite grim at this moment.
<fex>My mom</fex> is very loath to take any drugs without medical supervision.
Does biology really matter more than a willingness <fex>to take an active role in a child's life</fex>?
<fex>Mo</fex> decided to quit the program.
Mo decided <fex>to quit the program</fex>.
The State Cabinet <fex>today</fex> decided to file an appeal in the Supreme Court seeking an extension of six months for implementation of its judgment
<fex>At the first</fex> crossroad we decided to wait.
<fex>I</fex> set up a meeting with Carlos on Monday.
I'd like to set up <fex>a meeting with Mr. Hofmann</fex>.
Maria scheduled the appointment <fex>for Monday</fex>.
Gina scheduled a dentist appointment for Monday <fex>in Berkeley</fex>.
<fex>Rain</fex> is fairly unlikely today, I think.
There is a high chance of rain <fex>today</fex>.
There is a high chance of rain <fex>in Seattle</fex>.
<fex>The referee</fex> was totally biased against our team.
The umpire was partial <fex>to the home team</fex>.
The judge was neutral <fex>between the parties</fex>.
The judge favored the defendant <fex>over the plaintiff</fex>.
The judge made a biased <fex>decision</fex>.
My sister remained neutral <fex>in our disputes</fex>.
He had a neutral <fex>smile</fex> on his face.
